.TH px2ansi-rs 1  "px2ansi-rs 0.3.17" 
.SH NAME
px2ansi\-rs \- High\-fidelity terminal art engine and asset manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpx2ansi\-rs\fR [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-latency\fR] [\fB\-I\fR|\fB\-\-index\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
px2ansi\-rs converts images to ANSI terminal art using multiple rendering styles including half\-blocks, braille, ASCII density ramps, and CJK characters. It includes an image indexer with fuzzy search, interactive TUI browsing, and can export rendered art as PNG via a built\-in rasterizer.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-latency\fR
Show timing and execution metadata
.TP
\fB\-I\fR, \fB\-\-index\fR \fI<INDEX>\fR
Path to the JSON index file (overrides config file setting)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
px2ansi\-rs\-convert(1)
Convert a single image to ANSI/Unicode/Fade/Braille/Kanji/Full\-block/Ascii
.TP
px2ansi\-rs\-index(1)
Create a JSON index of a directory
.TP
px2ansi\-rs\-show(1)
Display a sprite from the index
.TP
px2ansi\-rs\-list(1)
List entries in the index
.TP
px2ansi\-rs\-completions(1)
Generate shell completions and add to your shell config. Example: `px2ansi\-rs completions bash >> ~/.bashrc`
.TP
px2ansi\-rs\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.3.17
